analysisPopulations.name: Screened Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who signed an informed consent form (ICF).

analysisPopulations.name: Enrolled Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who were enrolled in the study.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: FA
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who were enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug. The FA Set will be the primary population for all efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.description: All participants in the FA Set who have no major protocol deviations that would impact the primary efficacy endpoint. The PP Set will be used for sensitivity analyses of the primary efficacy endpoint.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of the Full Analysis Set with no major protocol deviations impacting the primary efficacy endpoint

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who received at least 1 dose of study drug. The Safety Set will be the primary population for all safety analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PK Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient plasma concentration data to derive at least 1 PK parameter. The PK Analysis Set will be used for all PK analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of the Safety Set with sufficient plasma concentration data to derive at least 1 PK parameter

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacodynamic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PD Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient PD data to derive at least 1 PD parameter. The PD Analysis Set will be used for all PD analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of the Safety Set with sufficient PD data to derive at least 1 PD parameter

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age calculated as of the date of informed consent.

characteristics.name: Body Mass Index (BMI)
characteristics.description: Body Mass Index (BMI) calculated as weight (kg)/[height (m)]^2.

characteristics.name: Duration of Wilson Disease (WD)
characteristics.description: Duration of Wilson Disease at baseline.

characteristics.name: Age at diagnosis of Wilson Disease (WD)
characteristics.description: Age at diagnosis of Wilson Disease.

characteristics.name: Wilson Disease (WD) phenotype
characteristics.description: Wilson Disease phenotype, categorized as hepatic, neurologic, or mixed.

characteristics.name: Serum ceruloplasmin
characteristics.description: Baseline laboratory value for serum ceruloplasmin.

characteristics.name: Serum copper
characteristics.description: Baseline laboratory value for serum copper.

characteristics.name: 24-hour urinary copper excretion
characteristics.description: Baseline laboratory value for 24-hour urinary copper excretion.

characteristics.name: Wilson Disease (WD) History
characteristics.description: A separate summary of Wilson Disease history.

characteristics.name: Prior medications
characteristics.description: Prior medications coded using the WHO Drug Dictionary.

characteristics.name: Concomitant medications
characteristics.description: Concomitant medications coded using the WHO Drug Dictionary.

characteristics.name: Prior medications used to treat Wilson Disease (WD)
characteristics.description: A separate summary of prior medications used to treat Wilson Disease.
